Class JCell

    java.awt.image.ImageObserver, java.awt.MenuContainer, java.io.Serializable, javax.accessibility.Accessible, javax.swing.SwingConstants

    public class JCell
extends javax.swing.JLabel
    JCell is a graphical representation of a Cell object. It's essentially a colored JLabel component with coloring according to its type
    See Also:
    Cell, JLabel, JCellGrid, Serialized Form

    • Method Detail

      • isOpen

        public boolean isOpen()
        Returns the "primitive" type of the JCell object (if open true, else false).
        Returns:
        the type of the JCell object.

      • isStart

        public boolean isStart()
        Returns true if this current JCell object is assigned as a start-cell. This is used when solving paths in a JCellGrid.
        Returns:
        true if this JCell object is a start-cell, false otherwise.

      • isFinish

        public boolean isFinish()
        Returns true if this current JCell object is assigned as a finish-cell. This is used when solving paths in a JCellGrid.
        Returns:
        true if this JCell object is a finish-cell, false otherwise.

      • isProcessed

        public boolean isProcessed()
        Returns true if this current JCell object is marked as processed. This is used when solving paths in a JCellGrid, or more explicitly, this is to note that the solving algorithm has processed this current JCell object.
        Returns:
        true if this JCell object is a processed, false otherwise.

      • isPartOfPath

        public boolean isPartOfPath()
        Returns true if this JCell object is marked as part of the path (generated by a pathsolving algorithm).
        Returns:
        true if this JCell object is a part of a path, false otherwise.

      • open

        public void open()
        This method sets the current JCell object to an open JCell object, i.e. setting the background color to white and makes it editable.
        See Also:
        JCellGrid, JCellMouseListener

      • close

        public void close()
        This method sets the current JCell object to a closed JCell object, i.e. setting the background color to grey and makes it non-editable.
        See Also:
        JCellGrid, JCellMouseListener

      • setToStart

        public void setToStart()
        This method marks the current JCell object as a startpoint JCell object, i.e. setting the background color to green and marking it as a startingpoint.
        See Also:
        JCellGrid, JCellMouseListener, JMazeWorker

      • setToFinish

        public void setToFinish()
        This method marks the current JCell object as a finishingpoint JCell object, i.e. setting the background color to red and marking it as a finishingpoint.
        See Also:
        JCellGrid, JCellMouseListener, JMazeWorker

      • processed

        public void processed()
        This method marks the current JCell object as a processed JCell object, i.e. setting the background color to [180, 180, 249] (in RGB) and marking it as processed (by the pathsolving algorithm).
        See Also:
        JCellGrid, JCellMouseListener, JMazeWorker

      • setToPath

        public void setToPath()
        This method marks the current JCell object as a part of a path JCell object, i.e. setting the background color to [80, 80, 249] (in RGB) and marking it as a part of a path generated by a pathsolving algorithm.
        See Also:
        JCellGrid, JCellMouseListener, JMazeWorker

      • getRow

        public int getRow()
        Returns the row position of this JCell object.
        Returns:
        the row position of this JCell object.

      • getColumn

        public int getColumn()
        Return the column position of this JCell object.
        Returns:
        the row position of this JCell object.
